Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

From the problem data at end date 2024-01-28:

- Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20
- No mention of long-term liabilities, so total liabilities = Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20
- Total Assets = 15,653,266.97

Step 1: Calculate the debt to asset ratio

Debt to Asset Ratio = 1,548,001.20 / 15,653,266.97 â‰ˆ 0.0989
